dcterms:creator: I. Olmeda
E. Fernandez
dcterms:description: The Spanish banks’ data is obtained from Olmeda and Fernandez (1997). The dataset contains 66 banks with 9 features, out of which 37 banks went bankrupt and 29 banks are healthy. The financial ratios are presented in the dataset, with data for failed banks taken from the last financial statements before bankruptcy was declared.
dcterms:title: Spanish banks

dcterms:creator: S. Canbas
A. Caubak
S. B. Kilic
dcterms:description: The Turkish banks’ data is available at the Turkish Banks Association. This dataset contains data of 40 banks, with 18 banks going bankrupt and 22 banks being healthy. The dataset includes 12 financial ratios chosen as early warning indicators for predicting bank health.
dcterms:title: Turkish banks

dcterms:creator: M. J. Beynon
M. J. Peel
dcterms:description: The UK banks’ data consists of 60 samples, with 30 being healthy and 30 bankrupt. This dataset is used to analyze the financial health of banks in the UK.
dcterms:title: UK banks
